                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.5200 Compañia Terrenos Y Ganados San
                    Rodrigo/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-11T21:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 11, 1939—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 244, December 11, 5 p.m.,<note
                        n="22" xml:id="d624fn22">Not printed.</note> Lie. Mena, Chief of the
                    Diplomatic Section, informed Gibson<note n="23" xml:id="d624fn23">Raleigh
                        Augustus Gibson, Second Secretary of Embassy.</note> that possession would
                    not be given December 12th and that the 30-day period for fencing had been
                    granted. American Consul at Piedras Negras informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
